22 conchyliatis peristromatis] ‘purple-dyed coverlets': conchylium was a light purple dye produced from a kind of shell-fish with an admixture of other ngredients. The patchwork coverlets (centones) ordinarily used by slaves were made of the commonest rags.

peristromatis] the word is a latinised form of περιστρώματα; for the form of the ablative‚ cp. poematis, epigrammatis, aenigmatis.

cellis] ‘garret', ‘hut’, a word peculiarly applied to the dwellings of slaves.
